      <title>Shopping and Daily Errands: Turkey vs Germany</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/germany/living/shopping-turkey-vs-germany/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/germany/living/shopping-turkey-vs-germany/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Shopping &amp;amp; Daily Errands: Turkey vs Germany&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;shopping--daily-errands-turkey-vs-germany&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#shopping--daily-errands-turkey-vs-germany&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sunday everything is closed. Yes, really. Here&amp;rsquo;s how to adapt — and what you might actually prefer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;🇹🇷 Turkey: Open, Loud, and Always Available&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;-turkey-open-loud-and-always-available&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#-turkey-open-loud-and-always-available&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Shopping in Turkey is a full sensory experience. Markets are open late, corner shops (&lt;em&gt;bakkal&lt;/em&gt;) are open almost around the clock, and if you run out of something at 11pm, there&amp;rsquo;s almost always somewhere to go.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
